<paragraph blockId="4.[225,1436,1814,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="14">
Genus of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2002" box="[501,669,1814,1840]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponticeratinae">Ponticeratinae</taxonomicName>
with extremely discoidal, subevolute conch. Without ventrolateral grooves. Suture line with relatively narrow external lobe, very low median saddle, very small E2 lobe, shallow and rounded lateral lobe. Suture line formula (E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[887,896,1905,1919]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="14">2</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[921,930,1905,1919]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="14">1</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[955,964,1905,1919]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="14">2</subScript>
) L: I.
</paragraph>
